The paper discusses the development of artificial general intelligence, which is a topic that falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses cognitive architectures, which are often used in the field of neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper discusses language and perception, which are topics that fall under the categories of natural language processing (cs.CL) and computer vision (cs.CV), respectively. Finally, the paper discusses the incorporation of cognitive biases into models of universal algorithmic intelligence, which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
